There's a public domain implementation of Blum, Blum, and
Shub's cryptographically strong random number generator
on the FTP server at Michigan State.  Watch and wait
(i.e. lurk) for a posting from Mark Riordan of MSU;
from time to time he mentions the complete FTP path.

Warning: this particular implenentation of B,B,&S is slow.
About ten bits per second.
